tspan.tspan: PCI DSS PAN remediation project
This project required me to create high level and low-level design documents for backend (Unisys Mainframe). Performed data
reconciliation and analysis using Python (with the pandas library) to further produce the high-level design. Pandas(python) was
used to reconcile 4 Million PANs across three systems. I also produced low level design for critical components and constructed
proof of concept code for the development team. Also performed review for Development and Test team artefacts. I worked
along with another designer to provide summary of discrepancies that we found during our analysis.
● Helped to remediate 4 million PANs stored in the Customer database
● Identified 250K incorrect credit cards that would cause issues with the PAN migration

tspan.style: font-weight:bold;font-family:'Eras Bold ITC';-inkscape-font-specification:'Eras Bold ITC Bold';fill:url(#linearGradient38226)

tspan.tspan: PAN Covid-19 Payment holiday
Due to temporary shutdown of work places and many small businesses, customers needed payment holiday to ensure that their
credit ratings were not impacted. Worked on an Agile project to implement changes in a personal loan system.
As part of this project, I created a tactical solution using python to extend personal loans to provide payment holidays for
customers. Further I created another suite of python programs that used SQLite database to re-write loans that could not be
extended further. The tactical solutions were used as a prototype to build the strategic solution on Unisys mainframe. I worked as
a lead for this project, while writing few COBOL programs and batch runstreams myself. From initial design to warranty support, I
was involved in reviews and discussions with third parties like Experian, Transunion and other Credit report agencies.
● Implemented a tactical solution very quickly to help the society to better serve it's customers
● Provided Payment holiday for around 50K customers during the Covid-19 pandemic

tspan.tspan: Money Laundering Regulation project
Due to new regulations in EU, client wanted to collect additional customer data related to Country of Birth and Employment. I
was involved in creating the batch designs and to work on a complex change in the customer de-duplication process.
Created design for batch and online programs on Unisys mainframe for Money laundering regulatory(MLR) project. Was involved
in reviewing Build and Test team work. Python was used to create test data for 11 million records to perform Volume test of the
migration process on the Unisys mainframe.
● Implemented API and database changes to MLR data in Unisys mainframe
● Implemented logic to de-duplicate customer information related to the new MLR data

tspan.style: font-weight:bold;font-family:'Eras Bold ITC';-inkscape-font-specification:'Eras Bold ITC Bold';fill:url(#linearGradient38226)

tspan.tspan: Batch explorer and cross reference tool
As a process improvement, I created a web application using python, Flask and SQLite that was hosted within the team. The idea
was to generate rich interactive diagrams using data from runstreams, batch scheduler and programs. This website front-end was
created using vis.js and jquery javascript libraries. I wrote multiple parsers to read runstreams, programs, database tables, copy
procs and sub-programs and populated a graph object that I created. This graph object was then used to generate the nodes and
edges for vis.js library based on the user query. Docker was used to create a container that is accessible by the team within the
company network.
After regular use of the tool, other engineers in the team have requested me to add more functionality. Schedule was created to
fetch the sources into the docker container on a regular basis.
● Easy UI to search for runstreams, programs and batch schedule
● Unified code bases and generated interactive diagram that could be used by the team to do impact analysis for future projects.

Development and Test teams. Managed a small team in UK and India.

● Identified and improved Customer De-duplication process and provided a savings of around £27,000 per year by reducing MIPS
